cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "JailGuard"
message: "If you use this software in research or production, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: "Yury"
    family-names: "Fedoseev"
url: "https://github.com/yfedoseev/jailguard"
repository-code: "https://github.com/yfedoseev/jailguard"
abstract: >-
  JailGuard is a pure-Rust prompt-injection detection library with a
  1.5 MB embedded ONNX classifier. It classifies inputs across 8
  attack categories (Benign, RolePlay, InstructionOverride,
  ContextManipulation, OutputManipulation, EncodingAttack,
  JailbreakPattern, PromptLeaking) with 98.40% accuracy on a
  7,049-sample held-out test set drawn from 17 public datasets.
  Runs CPU-only with sub-50ms inference, zero-config, with bindings
  for Rust, Python, JavaScript, and Go.
keywords:
  - prompt-injection
  - prompt-injection-detection
  - llm-security
  - ai-security
  - guardrails
  - jailbreak-detection
  - rust
  - onnx
  - machine-learning
